history.content:
In my experience, 188 and 170 fill up relatively fast. 186 isn't as popular. Unsure about 168

Keep in mind that the number of seats isn't necessarily representative of how popular the courses are. A course with fewer seats might do so because there is less interest, and thus would be easier to get into.

Although, this certainly isn't the case with 188: that's a surprisingly and unfortunately low seat count.

--------------------------------

children.subject: 168 is very popular, so I wouldn't count on that one. I got into 170 and 188 this semester (after the department declared me, I moved up the wait list and got into the classes).

history.content: The schedule planner shows that 170 has 612 seats, 186 has 525 seats, 168 has 510 seats, but 188 has only 297 seats? Which of these courses can undeclared students possibly get in?
